definition: to press against/to support/to prop up/to resist/to equal/to balance/to make up for/to mortgage/to arrive at/to clap (one's hands) lightly (expressing delight) (Taiwan pr. [zhi3] for this sense)
to touch/to make contact with sth/to stir up sb's emotions

sentences.english: A man never tells you anything until you contradict him.
sentences.chinese: 一个人永远不会给你什么启示，直到你跟他相抵触。

sentences.english: In retaliation, the Whigs expelled Tyler from their party.
sentences.chinese: 由于政见的抵触，泰勒被辉格党开除出党。

sentences.english: We humans seem to have a natural-born subject to change.
sentences.chinese: 我们人类似乎对变化有着天生的抵触心理。

sentences.english: Incentive plans can therefore mediate against change and responsiveness .
sentences.chinese: 激励计划因此会与改变和响应度相抵触。

sentences.english: Usually, that repugnance dissipates once people become familiar with new technologies.
sentences.chinese: 通常，一旦人们开始熟悉新技术，这种抵触就会消失。

sentences.english: It transforms a natural repugnance into a moral shock.
sentences.chinese: 它把一个自然的抵触转化为了一个道德的愤慨。

sentences.english: If a relationship is strong enough, its no big deal for arguements or conflicts.
sentences.chinese: 假设一段关系够稳定的话，争持和抵触只是小事。

sentences.english: Where any relevant provision conflicts with this document, the latter shall prevail.
sentences.chinese: 过去有关规定与此文件有抵触的一律以此文件为准。

sentences.english: Pretty much all mother-child relationships have some conflict built into them, some more than others.
sentences.chinese: 很多母子存在抵触关系，有一些甚至比这更严重。

sentences.english: But these are mostly untested and, in some cases, controversial.
sentences.chinese: 但是这些大多未经检验，并且在某些情况下相互抵触。

sentences.english: However, local policy may contradict this execution style for the pattern.
sentences.chinese: 但是，本地政策也许会抵触这种执行模式。

sentences.english: It tore against the social fabric of Roman society, and it offended the gods.
sentences.chinese: 与罗马的社会结构相抵触，还冒犯了诸神。

sentences.english: We should recant all opinions which are in conflict with those proclaimed by the central leadership.
sentences.chinese: 我们应当放弃所有与中央领导所宣布的有抵触的意见。

sentences.english: The hours of those two exams conflict.
sentences.chinese: 那两门测验的钟点互有抵触。

sentences.english: Expect resistance to talking about emotionally charged issues surrounding suicidality, he said.
sentences.chinese: 对讨论自杀话题时的抵触情绪要有心理准备，他说。

sentences.english: Thought keeping staff may conflict with the new thing fetching in.
sentences.chinese: 思想保守的民警可能抵触新事物的引进等。
